                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d810">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Eddy</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-11-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 5, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Eddy reports that the American consuls at Riga and Rostoff have asked for
                    military protection. The same has been asked for and has been obtained for Riga
                    and will also be given to the consulate at Rostoff. The consul at Odessa reports
                    that severe conflicts between Jews and Russians were begun by the Jews. The
                    fighting is still going on and probably thousands of the Jews were killed.
                    American interests at that place are not threatened. The situation at Warsaw is
                    serious. Conflicts continue between the Poles and the Russian army. At Moscow
                    everything is quiet. The people have resumed work at St. Petersburg. A large
                    meeting occurred to-day without conflict after the funeral service of those
                    killed in recent disturbances. Large crowds assembled, composed principally of
                    sightseers. Important concessions have been made to Finland.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
